<br>
I have been working this skill since lvl 8. I am now lvl 22 and working all electrum combo's.  It is highly profitable to be able to enchant the metal you are working:<br>
<br>
1.  you get more pp per success on buyback<br>
2.  helps keep skills capped and helps improve             specialization in alteration(only after lvl 16) <br>
3.  when you get to the highend metals i.e. gold and plat, in your spell book you will start seeing intellegence buffs(meaning less failures;very important for 110pp per plat bar)<br>
<br>
ALWAYS stick close to the trivail charts...some have wrong lvls  on them, but i use the theory of if i am withing 1 of the cap on that combo move to the next.  It has always been my experience that the cap lvl is the hardest to attain, when you are working the combo to be capped.  BASICALLY, always stay ahead of the chart by 1 but follow it close.<br>
<br>
