<br>
I agree, this is where I made most of my profit back when enchanting the bars and getting extra money back. Unfortunately if you're not trivial to the gem and bar you lose a lot and getting 4pp back after each successful combine is not enough to make up the loss of 105pp for a plat bar and 138 (or so) pp for a ruby. <br>
<br>
Enchanting bars also takes a lot of mana out of you, especially if you're trying to enchant multiple stacks of plat bars. I found it hard to keep mana up at lvl 55 where I already also had clarity II. I started powerleveling my jewelry skill up to 250 by just buying and combining. Now at the skill of 250, I have lost about 12pp just buy buying and raising my skill WITHOUT enchanting the bar. <br>
<br>
All in all I can say it's worth it, I hardly get failures, and I get the best chance when combining velium blue diamond and diamond, the odds are in my favor so far. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><br><center><img src=http://home.dencity.com/ladylimelight/legendlogo2final.jpg><html><h5></center>
